This paper deals with computational properties of voting rules, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also proposes approximation methods for manipulating the rules, which involves algorithms and optimization techniques, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the complexity of manipulating the rules, which involves computational complexity theory, making it relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
